text:
$14 an hour x 40 hours a week x 52 weeks = $29,120

1/@McDonalds won't go out of business, $1 will simply move to a $2 menu

2/Minimum-wage workers save ~$0--it all goes to living expenses! This increase will only drive monetary velocity (i.e. folks will buy more McDonalds)

City/State MW varies: Seattle, NYC, SF, LA are at $15--DOUBLE the federal MW 

I believe in free-markets, but not increasing the minimum wage for 11 years is absurd

My modest proposal: a 10% increase per year for 7 years gets us to ~$14: let's do it & see what happens!
